CVE-2010-1256.summary: Unspecified vulnerability in Microsoft IIS 6.0, 7.0, and 7.5, when Extended Protection for Authentication is enabled, allows remote authenticated users to execute arbitrary code via unknown vectors related to "token checking" that trigger memory corruption, aka "IIS Authentication Memory Corruption Vulnerability."

CVE-2010-2730.summary: Buffer overflow in Microsoft Internet Information Services (IIS) 7.5, when FastCGI is enabled, allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code via crafted headers in a request, aka "Request Header Buffer Overflow Vulnerability."

CVE-2010-3972.summary: Heap-based buffer overflow in the TELNET_STREAM_CONTEXT::OnSendData function in ftpsvc.dll in Microsoft FTP Service 7.0 and 7.5 for Internet Information Services (IIS) 7.0, and IIS 7.5, allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code or cause a denial of service (daemon crash) via a crafted FTP command, aka "IIS FTP Service Heap Buffer Overrun Vulnerability." NOTE: some of these details are obtained from third party information.

CVE-2010-1899.summary: Stack consumption vulnerability in the ASP implementation in Microsoft Internet Information Services (IIS) 5.1, 6.0, 7.0, and 7.5 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (daemon outage) via a crafted request, related to asp.dll, aka "IIS Repeated Parameter Request Denial of Service Vulnerability."

CVE-2012-2531.summary: Microsoft Internet Information Services (IIS) 7.5 uses weak permissions for the Operational log, which allows local users to discover credentials by reading this file, aka "Password Disclosure Vulnerability."

                        <section id="city_news">
                          <h1>city news</h1>

                            
                                    <p class="featuretype">
                                        Annual Egg Hunt Scheduled for April 13, Volunteers Needed
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
											<table><tr><td style="display:none;">
											<img src='' width="100" height="75"></td>
											<td>Apr 05, 2019 - The Recreation and Parks Department will host the 2019 Egg Hunt on Saturday, April 13, in A.K. Bissell Park beginning at 11 a.m. Over 15,000 candy and prize-filled eggs will be hidden inside the park.<br /></td></tr>
                                        <tr><td colspan="2" align="right"><a href='content.aspx?article=4623'>read more »</a></td></tr></table><br>
                                        <hr/>
                                    </p>
									
                                
                                    <p class="featuretype">
                                        Students Host Virtual Open Forum for Intersection Improvement Project
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
											<table><tr><td style="display:none;">
											<img src='' width="100" height="75"></td>
											<td>Mar 30, 2019 - UT students are planning a virtual open forum as they continue to explore alternative designs for the intersection at Pennsylvania and North Tulane Avenues. The event will be accessible via Facebook Live on April 3.<br /></td></tr>
                                        <tr><td colspan="2" align="right"><a href='content.aspx?article=4621'>read more »</a></td></tr></table><br>
                                        <hr/>
                                    </p>
									
                                
                                    <p class="featuretype">
                                        Planning Commission Approves City Blueprint
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
											<table><tr><td style="display:none;">
											<img src='' width="100" height="75"></td>
											<td>Mar 27, 2019 - The Oak Ridge Municipal Planning Commission approved the City Blueprint Plan at its most recent meeting on March 21. The full document is now available for review on the City’s website.<br /></td></tr>
                                        <tr><td colspan="2" align="right"><a href='content.aspx?article=4619'>read more »</a></td></tr></table><br>
                                        <hr/>
                                    </p>
									
                                
                                    <p class="featuretype">
                                        NOTICE: Oak Ridge Civic Center Planned Water Outage
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
											<table><tr><td style="display:none;">
											<img src='' width="100" height="75"></td>
											<td>Mar 25, 2019 - The Oak Ridge Civic Center will be without water on Wednesday, March 27, between approximately 9 a.m. and 1 p.m. while crews make repairs to the water line that services the building.<br /></td></tr>
                                        <tr><td colspan="2" align="right"><a href='content.aspx?article=4617'>read more »</a></td></tr></table><br>
                                        <hr/>
                                    </p>
									
                                
                                    <p class="featuretype">
                                        Oak Ridge Student Receives Fire Safety Award
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
											<table><tr><td style="display:none;">
											<img src='' width="100" height="75"></td>
											<td>Mar 21, 2019 - The City of Oak Ridge, Oak Ridge Fire Department, and Oak Ridge Police Department recognized a local student on March 21 for his quick actions to stop a fire from spreading inside his home last year.<br /></td></tr>
                                        <tr><td colspan="2" align="right"><a href='content.aspx?article=4616'>read more »</a></td></tr></table><br>
                                        <hr/>
                                    </p>
									
                                
                                    <p class="featuretype">
                                        Celebrate National Library Week in Oak Ridge
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
											<table><tr><td style="display:none;">
											<img src='' width="100" height="75"></td>
											<td>Mar 20, 2019 - This April, the Oak Ridge Public Library (ORPL) joins libraries of all types in celebrating the many ways libraries build strong communities by providing critical resources, programs and expertise. Events are scheduled for April 4, 9 and 11.<br /></td></tr>
                                        <tr><td colspan="2" align="right"><a href='content.aspx?article=4615'>read more »</a></td></tr></table><br>
                                        <hr/>
                                    </p>
									
                                
                                    <p class="featuretype">
                                        Oak Ridge Summer Camp Registration Begins April 1
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
											<table><tr><td style="display:none;">
											<img src='' width="100" height="75"></td>
											<td>Mar 19, 2019 - Registration for the 2019 Summer Camp sponsored by the City of Oak Ridge Recreation and Parks Department will begin Monday, April 1. Early registration is recommended as space is limited and the camp will fill up quickly.<br /></td></tr>
                                        <tr><td colspan="2" align="right"><a href='content.aspx?article=4614'>read more »</a></td></tr></table><br>
                                        <hr/>
                                    </p>

								<a href='content.aspx?page=39'>Read City News Archives »</a>
							</p>
